
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 89/120 – SCD Type 2

🎤 Interview Question

You have the following target table:

customer_id	city	start_date	end_date	is_current

101	Hyderabad	2023-01-01	NULL	Y


The source contains:

customer_id	city

101	Bangalore


Implement SCD Type 2.


---

✅ Expected Output

Existing Record

customer_id	city	start_date	end_date	is_current

101	Hyderabad	2023-01-01	2024-06-30	N


New Record

customer_id	city	start_date	end_date	is_current

101	Bangalore	2024-07-01	NULL	Y



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import col, lit, current_date

# Close existing record
expired_df = (
    target_df.filter(col("is_current") == "Y")
             .join(source_df, "customer_id")
             .filter(target_df.city != source_df.city)
             .withColumn("end_date", current_date())
             .withColumn("is_current", lit("N"))
)

# Insert new record
new_df = (
    source_df.withColumn("start_date", current_date())
             .withColumn("end_date", lit(None))
             .withColumn("is_current", lit("Y"))
)


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Difference between SCD Type 1 and Type 2?

Answer

SCD Type 1	SCD Type 2

Overwrites old value	Keeps history
No history	Full history
One record	Multiple records
Faster	More storage



---

Q2. Why use is_current?

Answer

It helps identify the active version of a record quickly without checking dates.


---

Q3. Where is SCD Type 2 used?

Answer

Customer address history

Employee salary history

Product price history

Account status history



